Linux VPN Server Setup
ProtectWave VPN will use Ubuntu Linux as the operating system for all VPN servers.

Operating System:
Ubuntu 22.04 LTS

Setup Objectives:

Create secure Linux server instance in AWS
Enable secure remote access
Apply system updates
Configure firewall rules
Prepare system for WireGuard installation

Security Measures:

SSH based access only
Firewall enabled
Minimal open ports
System logging enabled

Purpose:

This step ensures the VPN server is stable, secure, and ready for VPN protocol configuration in the next phase.
